Charle: Hoho...then, if you girls just throw it into the air, it'll...
Gotthold: Professor Ceres!
Charle: Oh! So it's you, Gotthold.
Charle: Why do you look so exhausted?
Gotthold: I did just get done with Professor Dietrich's class.

Gotthold: All he does is scribble down a bunch of runes then tells us to practice them. Yet he never properly explains any of it. 
It's like he's living in his own little world where we're all geniuses. He expects us to just understand everything...
Charle: Don't think about it too much. You just have to keep working hard.
？？？: Come on, don't let us Life Magic folks down!
？？？: How dare they pick a fight against us Applied Magic people? I'll teach him a lesson!
Gotthold: What is going on?
Male Academy Pupil: Leafy Algae Ball, go get her!
Female Academy Pupil: Hmph, don't you look down on Applied Magic!
Male Academy Pupil: ...Damn, I'll show you what an enhanced Life Magic Rune is capable of!
Female Academy Pupil: You don't know when to give up, do you!?
Female Academy Pupil: It didn't take any damage!?
Charle: Both of you, stop right now!
Female Academy Pupil: P-Professor!? He started it...
Female Academy Pupil: He said that we Applied Magic people only make useless toys!
Charle: And you think that means you're allowed to violate the Academy's rules!?
Gotthold: Professor, look out! Behind you!
Charle: Rest assured. It merely fainted. I didn't attack its vitals.
Charle: When enhanced magic is cast directly on living creatures, it can easily cause the creature to enter an unstable mental state.
Charle: You need to be careful before you learn how to fully utilize it.
Morris: Hey, why are you meddling in this?
Charle: Morris Dietrich, you were standing right there. Why didn't you interfere?
Morris: It's just a friendly match between students. What's wrong with that?
Charle: If they truly want a match, they should follow the rules and apply for a simulation battle. Besides, aren't you worried about the students' safety?
Morris: Even if they do get injured, they can rely on us Life Magic folks to heal them. So, as long as they don't die, all is well. Haha~
Charle: You...
Morris: The runes on this beast...is this how I usually teach this? Hey, Clovis!
Morris: Demonstrate to this idiot; show him how to fix this rune that's riddled with newbie errors.
Aosta: Understood.
Aosta: All done, professor Dietrich.
Morris: Perfect as always. I expect no less from my disciple~
Morris: Hey you, at least be one-tenth as capable as Clovis so you can have SOMETHING to prove your value at the Academy...
Morris: ...Still standing?
Morris: Could it be that you know arcane magic that can improve your grades by just standing there?
Charle: Nothing to see here. Students, return to the classroom to prepare for the next class.
Gotthold: Professor...
Charle: Gotthold, you should also take your leave.
Gotthold: Okay...
Morris: You want to say something to me?
Charle: Your action just now will give that student nothing but a sense of inferiority. I hope you can improve your teaching attitude in the future.
Morris: Those with no talent shall be taught in a way that corresponds to their lack of talent.
Morris: If I were to teach like you and act all goody-two-shoes, I'd just be making myself more tired than I should be.
Charle: ...Watch your manners. Do you not know what "respect" means?
Morris: If you're that mad...
Morris: "If they truly want a match, they should follow the rules and apply for a simulation battle." Those were your exact words~
Charle: I had hoped for a more peaceful method to resolve this. However, if my victory means you can keep your attitude towards students in check,
Charle: Then I accept the challenge!
Charle: Come on!
Morris: Hmph...a match with you?
Morris: This is going to be over in seconds. Haha~
Charle: You lost the simulation battle!
Morris: Hmph...
Charle: Dietrich, don't forget your promise!
Morris: Shut it, you ass!
